Linux File System Navigation & Text Processing Log

Objective

Consolidated operational log based on analyzed material. Focus: navigating filesystem, locating files, and extracting/analyzing data using core Linux utilities.

⸻

1. File Discovery (find)

Structure

find [path] [options] [expression]

Usage Patterns
	•	Find by name:

find /home -name "file.txt"

	•	Case-insensitive:

find /home -iname "file.txt"

	•	Find directories:

find / -type d -name "logs"

	•	Find by size:

find / -size +100M

	•	Find and delete:

find /tmp -name "*.tmp" -delete

Insight

Used for filesystem enumeration and targeting files for analysis or cleanup.

⸻

2. Permissions Model (4,2,1 System)

Permission Values
	•	Read (r) = 4
	•	Write (w) = 2
	•	Execute (x) = 1

Structure

Owner | Group | Others

Example

chmod 755 file

→ Owner: rwx (7)
→ Group: r-x (5)
→ Others: r-x (5)

Insight

Defines access control during navigation and execution.

⸻

3. Text Searching (grep)

Structure

grep [options] pattern file

Usage Patterns
	•	Basic search:

grep "error" logfile.txt

	•	Case-insensitive:

grep -i "error" logfile.txt

	•	Recursive:

grep -r "password" /etc

	•	Show line numbers:

grep -n "error" file.txt

	•	Invert match:

grep -v "Port" file

Insight

Primary tool for filtering relevant data from files/logs.

⸻

4. Column Extraction (cut)

Usage Patterns
	•	By character:

cut -c 1-10 file.txt

	•	By delimiter:

cut -d "," -f 1 file.csv

	•	Multiple fields:

cut -d "," -f 1,2 file.csv

Insight

Used for simple structured extraction, limited compared to awk.

⸻

5. Sorting & Deduplication (sort, uniq)

Usage Patterns
	•	Sort data:

sort file.txt

	•	Unique values:

sort file.txt | uniq

	•	Count occurrences:

sort file.txt | uniq -c

Insight

Used for pattern detection and frequency analysis.

⸻

6. Structured Processing (awk)

Field-Based Parsing

awk -F: '{ print $1 }' file

Extract Multiple Fields

awk -F: '{ print $1, $7 }' /etc/passwd

Conditional Filtering

awk -F: '$1=="dave" { print $1, $7 }' /etc/passwd

Input Methods

awk -F: '{ print $7 }' /etc/passwd

or

< /etc/passwd awk -F: '{ print $7 }'

Insight

awk acts as:
	•	filter
	•	parser
	•	processor

⸻

7. Text Transformation (sed, tr)

Replace text

sed 's/old/new/' file

Replace globally

sed 's/old/new/g' file

Character translation

tr a o

Insight

Used for modifying and transforming data streams.

⸻

8. Pipeline Architecture

Core Concept

command | command | command

Example Workflow

awk -F: '{ print $7 }' /etc/passwd | sort | uniq -c

Execution Flow
	1.	Extract shell field
	2.	Sort values
	3.	Count occurrences

Output Example

2 /bin/bash
2 /bin/false
5 /sbin/nologin


⸻

9. Practical Navigation + Analysis Workflow

Example 1: Find and inspect files

find /var/log -name "*.log"

Example 2: Search inside files

grep -i "error" /var/log/syslog

Example 3: Extract structured data

grep dave /etc/passwd | cut -d: -f1,7

Optimized

awk -F: '$1=="dave" { print $1, $7 }' /etc/passwd


⸻

10. Advanced Data Pipeline

grep dave /etc/passwd \
| awk -F: '{ print $1, $7 }' \
| sort \
| uniq -c

Purpose
	•	Filter user
	•	Extract fields
	•	Analyze usage

